{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"You know, culture was born of the imagination,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and the imagination -- the imagination as we know it --"},{"time":7000,"text":"came into being when our species descended"},{"time":10000,"text":"from our progenitor, Homo erectus,"},{"time":13000,"text":"and, infused with consciousness, began a journey that would carry it"},{"time":16000,"text":"to every corner of the habitable world."},{"time":19000,"text":"For a time, we shared the stage with our distant cousins, Neanderthal,"},{"time":22000,"text":"who clearly had some spark of awareness,"},{"time":24000,"text":"but -- whether it was the increase in the size of the brain,"},{"time":27000,"text":"or the development of language,"},{"time":29000,"text":"or some other evolutionary catalyst --"},{"time":31000,"text":"we quickly left Neanderthal gasping for survival."},{"time":35000,"text":"By the time the last Neanderthal disappeared in Europe,"},{"time":38000,"text":"27,000 years ago,"},{"time":40000,"text":"our direct ancestors had already,"},{"time":42000,"text":"and for 5,000 years,"},{"time":44000,"text":"been crawling into the belly of the earth,"},{"time":46000,"text":"where in the light of the flickers of tallow candles,"},{"time":49000,"text":"they had brought into being"},{"time":51000,"text":"the great art of the Upper Paleolithic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53000,"text":"And I spent two months in the caves of southwest France"},{"time":56000,"text":"with the poet Clayton Eshleman, who wrote a beautiful book called \"Juniper Fuse.\""},{"time":59000,"text":"And you could look at this art and you could, of course,"},{"time":61000,"text":"see the complex social organization"},{"time":63000,"text":"of the people who brought it into being."},{"time":65000,"text":"But more importantly, it spoke of a deeper yearning,"},{"time":68000,"text":"something far more sophisticated than hunting magic."},{"time":71000,"text":"And the way Clayton put it was this way."},{"time":73000,"text":"He said, \"You know, clearly at some point,"},{"time":77000,"text":"we were all of an animal nature, and at some point, we weren't.\""},{"time":79000,"text":"And he viewed proto-shamanism as a kind of original attempt,"},{"time":81000,"text":"through ritual, to rekindle a connection"},{"time":84000,"text":"that had been irrevocably lost."},{"time":86000,"text":"So, he saw this art not as"},{"time":89000,"text":"hunting magic, but as postcards of nostalgia."},{"time":93000,"text":"And viewed in that light,"},{"time":95000,"text":"it takes on a whole other resonance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97000,"text":"And the most amazing thing about the Upper Paleolithic art"},{"time":99000,"text":"is that as an aesthetic expression,"},{"time":102000,"text":"it lasted for almost 20,000 years."},{"time":105000,"text":"If these were postcards of nostalgia,"},{"time":108000,"text":"ours was a very long farewell indeed."},{"time":111000,"text":"And it was also the beginning of our discontent,"},{"time":113000,"text":"because if you wanted to distill all of our experience"},{"time":115000,"text":"since the Paleolithic, it would come down to two words:"},{"time":118000,"text":"how and why."},{"time":120000,"text":"And these are the slivers of insight upon which cultures have been forged."},{"time":123000,"text":"Now, all people share the same"},{"time":125000,"text":"raw, adaptive imperatives."},{"time":127000,"text":"We all have children."},{"time":129000,"text":"We all have to deal with the mystery of death,"},{"time":131000,"text":"the world that waits beyond death,"},{"time":133000,"text":"the elders who fall away into their elderly years."},{"time":136000,"text":"All of this is part of our common experience,"},{"time":138000,"text":"and this shouldn't surprise us, because, after all,"},{"time":140000,"text":"biologists have finally proven it to be true,"},{"time":142000,"text":"something that philosophers have always dreamt to be true."},{"time":145000,"text":"And that is the fact that we are all brothers and sisters."},{"time":147000,"text":"We are all cut from the same genetic cloth."},{"time":150000,"text":"All of humanity, probably, is descended from a thousand people"},{"time":153000,"text":"who left Africa roughly 70,000 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"But the corollary of that is that,"},{"time":158000,"text":"if we all are brothers and sisters"},{"time":160000,"text":"and share the same genetic material,"},{"time":162000,"text":"all human populations share the same raw human genius,"},{"time":164000,"text":"the same intellectual acuity."},{"time":166000,"text":"And so whether that genius is placed"},{"time":168000,"text":"into -- technological wizardry"},{"time":170000,"text":"has been the great achievement of the West --"},{"time":173000,"text":"or by contrast, into unraveling the complex threads"},{"time":176000,"text":"of memory inherent in a myth,"},{"time":178000,"text":"is simply a matter of choice and cultural orientation."},{"time":180000,"text":"There is no progression of affairs"},{"time":182000,"text":"in human experience."},{"time":184000,"text":"There is no trajectory of progress. There's no pyramid"},{"time":186000,"text":"that conveniently places Victorian England at the apex"},{"time":189000,"text":"and descends down the flanks"},{"time":191000,"text":"to the so-called primitives of the world."},{"time":193000,"text":"All peoples are simply cultural options,"},{"time":196000,"text":"different visions of life itself."},{"time":198000,"text":"But what do I mean by different visions of life"},{"time":200000,"text":"making for completely different"},{"time":202000,"text":"possibilities for existence?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"Well, let's slip for a moment into the greatest culture sphere"},{"time":206000,"text":"ever brought into being by the imagination,"},{"time":209000,"text":"that of Polynesia."},{"time":211000,"text":"10,000 square kilometers,"},{"time":213000,"text":"tens of thousands of islands flung like jewels upon the southern sea."},{"time":216000,"text":"I recently sailed on the Hokulea,"},{"time":218000,"text":"named after the sacred star of Hawaii,"},{"time":221000,"text":"throughout the South Pacific to make a film"},{"time":223000,"text":"about the navigators."},{"time":225000,"text":"These are men and women who, even today, can name"},{"time":227000,"text":"250 stars in the night sky."},{"time":229000,"text":"These are men and women who can sense the presence of distant atolls"},{"time":232000,"text":"of islands beyond the visible horizon,"},{"time":235000,"text":"simply by watching the reverberation of waves"},{"time":237000,"text":"across the hull of their vessel, knowing full well"},{"time":239000,"text":"that every island group in the Pacific"},{"time":241000,"text":"has its unique refractive pattern"},{"time":243000,"text":"that can be read with the same perspicacity"},{"time":246000,"text":"with which a forensic scientist would read a fingerprint."},{"time":249000,"text":"These are sailors who in the darkness, in the hull of the vessel,"},{"time":251000,"text":"can distinguish as many as 32 different sea swells"},{"time":254000,"text":"moving through the canoe at any one point in time,"},{"time":257000,"text":"distinguishing local wave disturbances"},{"time":259000,"text":"from the great currents that pulsate across the ocean,"},{"time":262000,"text":"that can be followed with the same ease"},{"time":264000,"text":"that a terrestrial explorer would follow a river to the sea."},{"time":267000,"text":"Indeed, if you took all of the genius"},{"time":269000,"text":"that allowed us to put a man on the moon"},{"time":271000,"text":"and applied it to an understanding of the ocean,"},{"time":273000,"text":"what you would get is Polynesia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275000,"text":"And if we slip from the realm of the sea"},{"time":277000,"text":"into the realm of the spirit of the imagination,"},{"time":280000,"text":"you enter the realm of Tibetan Buddhism."},{"time":282000,"text":"And I recently made a film called \"The Buddhist Science of the Mind.\""},{"time":285000,"text":"Why did we use that word, science?"},{"time":288000,"text":"What is science but the empirical pursuit of the truth?"},{"time":290000,"text":"What is Buddhism but 2,500 years"},{"time":292000,"text":"of empirical observation"},{"time":294000,"text":"as to the nature of mind?"},{"time":296000,"text":"I travelled for a month in Nepal with our good friend, Matthieu Ricard,"},{"time":299000,"text":"and you'll remember Matthieu famously said to all of us"},{"time":301000,"text":"here once at TED,"},{"time":303000,"text":"\"Western science is a major response to minor needs.\""},{"time":306000,"text":"We spend all of our lifetime trying to live to be 100"},{"time":308000,"text":"without losing our teeth."},{"time":310000,"text":"The Buddhist spends all their lifetime trying to understand the nature of existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313000,"text":"Our billboards celebrate naked children in underwear."},{"time":315000,"text":"Their billboards are manuals,"},{"time":317000,"text":"prayers to the well-being of all sentient creatures."},{"time":320000,"text":"And with the blessing of Trulshik Rinpoche, we began a pilgrimage"},{"time":322000,"text":"to a curious destination,"},{"time":324000,"text":"accompanied by a great doctor."},{"time":326000,"text":"And the destination was a single room in a nunnery,"},{"time":329000,"text":"where a woman had gone into lifelong retreat"},{"time":331000,"text":"55 years before."},{"time":334000,"text":"And en route, we took darshan from Rinpoche,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and he sat with us and told us about the Four Noble Truths,"},{"time":340000,"text":"the essence of the Buddhist path."},{"time":342000,"text":"All life is suffering. That doesn't mean all life is negative."},{"time":345000,"text":"It means things happen."},{"time":347000,"text":"The cause of suffering is ignorance."},{"time":349000,"text":"By that, the Buddha did not mean stupidity;"},{"time":351000,"text":"he meant clinging to the illusion"},{"time":353000,"text":"that life is static and predictable."},{"time":355000,"text":"The third noble truth said that ignorance can be overcome."},{"time":357000,"text":"And the fourth and most important, of course,"},{"time":359000,"text":"was the delineation of a contemplative practice"},{"time":361000,"text":"that not only had the possibility"},{"time":363000,"text":"of a transformation of the human heart,"},{"time":365000,"text":"but had 2,500 years of empirical evidence"},{"time":368000,"text":"that such a transformation was a certainty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371000,"text":"And so, when this door opened onto the face of a woman"},{"time":373000,"text":"who had not been out of that room in 55 years,"},{"time":376000,"text":"you did not see a mad woman."},{"time":378000,"text":"You saw a woman who was more clear"},{"time":380000,"text":"than a pool of water in a mountain stream."},{"time":383000,"text":"And of course, this is what the Tibetan monks told us."},{"time":387000,"text":"They said, at one point, you know, we don't really believe"},{"time":390000,"text":"you went to the moon, but you did."},{"time":392000,"text":"You may not believe that we achieve enlightenment"},{"time":394000,"text":"in one lifetime, but we do."},{"time":397000,"text":"And if we move from the realm of the spirit"},{"time":399000,"text":"to the realm of the physical,"},{"time":401000,"text":"to the sacred geography of Peru --"},{"time":403000,"text":"I've always been interested in the relationships of indigenous people"},{"time":406000,"text":"that literally believe that the Earth is alive,"},{"time":408000,"text":"responsive to all of their aspirations,"},{"time":410000,"text":"all of their needs."},{"time":412000,"text":"And, of course, the human population"},{"time":414000,"text":"has its own reciprocal obligations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416000,"text":"I spent 30 years living amongst"},{"time":418000,"text":"the people of Chinchero"},{"time":420000,"text":"and I always heard about an event that I always wanted to participate in."},{"time":423000,"text":"Once each year, the fastest young boy"},{"time":426000,"text":"in each hamlet is given the honor of becoming a woman."},{"time":429000,"text":"And for one day, he wears the clothing of his sister"},{"time":431000,"text":"and he becomes a transvestite,"},{"time":433000,"text":"a waylaka. And for that day,"},{"time":435000,"text":"he leads all able-bodied men on a run,"},{"time":438000,"text":"but it's not your ordinary run."},{"time":440000,"text":"You start off at 11,500 feet."},{"time":443000,"text":"You run down to the base of the sacred mountain, Antakillqa."},{"time":445000,"text":"You run up to 15,000 feet,"},{"time":447000,"text":"descend 3,000 feet."},{"time":449000,"text":"Climb again over the course of 24 hours."},{"time":452000,"text":"And of course, the waylakama spin,"},{"time":454000,"text":"the trajectory of the route,"},{"time":456000,"text":"is marked by holy mounds of Earth,"},{"time":458000,"text":"where coke is given to the Earth, libations of alcohol to the wind,"},{"time":461000,"text":"the vortex of the feminine is brought to the mountaintop."},{"time":464000,"text":"And the metaphor is clear: you go into the mountain as an individual,"},{"time":467000,"text":"but through exhaustion, through sacrifice,"},{"time":470000,"text":"you emerge as a community that has once again"},{"time":472000,"text":"reaffirmed its sense of place in the planet."},{"time":475000,"text":"And at 48, I was the only outsider ever to go through this,"},{"time":478000,"text":"only one to finish it."},{"time":480000,"text":"I only managed to do it by chewing more coca leaves in one day"},{"time":483000,"text":"than anyone in the 4,000-year history of the plant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487000,"text":"But these localized rituals become pan-Andean,"},{"time":489000,"text":"and these fantastic festivals,"},{"time":491000,"text":"like that of the Qoyllur Rit'i, which occurs"},{"time":493000,"text":"when the Pleiades reappear in the winter sky."},{"time":496000,"text":"It's kind of like an Andean Woodstock:"},{"time":498000,"text":"60,000 Indians on pilgrimage"},{"time":500000,"text":"to the end of a dirt road"},{"time":502000,"text":"that leads to the sacred valley, called the Sinakara,"},{"time":504000,"text":"which is dominated by three tongues"},{"time":506000,"text":"of the great glacier."},{"time":508000,"text":"The metaphor is so clear. You bring the crosses from your community,"},{"time":511000,"text":"in this wonderful fusion of Christian"},{"time":513000,"text":"and pre-Columbian ideas."},{"time":515000,"text":"You place the cross into the ice,"},{"time":517000,"text":"in the shadow of Ausangate, the most sacred of all Apus,"},{"time":520000,"text":"or sacred mountains of the Inca."},{"time":522000,"text":"And then you do the ritual dances that empower the crosses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"Now, these ideas and these events"},{"time":527000,"text":"allow us even to deconstruct iconic places"},{"time":530000,"text":"that many of you have been to, like Machu Picchu."},{"time":532000,"text":"Machu Picchu was never a lost city."},{"time":534000,"text":"On the contrary, it was completely linked in"},{"time":536000,"text":"to the 14,000 kilometers of royal roads"},{"time":539000,"text":"the Inca made in less than a century."},{"time":541000,"text":"But more importantly, it was linked in"},{"time":543000,"text":"to the Andean notions of sacred geography."},{"time":546000,"text":"The intiwatana, the hitching post to the sun,"},{"time":549000,"text":"is actually an obelisk that constantly reflects the light"},{"time":552000,"text":"that falls on the sacred Apu of Machu Picchu,"},{"time":555000,"text":"which is Sugarloaf Mountain, called Huayna Picchu."},{"time":558000,"text":"If you come to the south of the intiwatana, you find an altar."},{"time":561000,"text":"Climb Huayna Picchu, find another altar."},{"time":563000,"text":"Take a direct north-south bearing,"},{"time":565000,"text":"you find to your astonishment"},{"time":567000,"text":"that it bisects the intiwatana stone,"},{"time":569000,"text":"goes to the skyline,"},{"time":571000,"text":"hits the heart of Salcantay, the second of the most important mountains"},{"time":574000,"text":"of the Incan empire."},{"time":576000,"text":"And then beyond Salcantay, of course,"},{"time":578000,"text":"when the southern cross reaches the southernmost point in the sky,"},{"time":581000,"text":"directly in that same alignment, the Milky Way overhead."},{"time":584000,"text":"But what is enveloping Machu Picchu from below?"},{"time":587000,"text":"The sacred river, the Urubamba, or the Vilcanota,"},{"time":590000,"text":"which is itself the Earthly equivalent of the Milky Way,"},{"time":593000,"text":"but it's also the trajectory that Viracocha walked"},{"time":596000,"text":"at the dawn of time when he brought the universe into being."},{"time":599000,"text":"And where does the river rise?"},{"time":601000,"text":"Right on the slopes of the Koariti."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605000,"text":"So, 500 years after Columbus,"},{"time":607000,"text":"these ancient rhythms of landscape"},{"time":610000,"text":"are played out in ritual."},{"time":612000,"text":"Now, when I was here at the first TED,"},{"time":614000,"text":"I showed this photograph: two men of the Elder Brothers,"},{"time":617000,"text":"the descendants, survivors of El Dorado."},{"time":620000,"text":"These, of course, are the descendants"},{"time":623000,"text":"of the ancient Tairona civilization."},{"time":626000,"text":"If those of you who are here remember that I mentioned"},{"time":628000,"text":"that they remain ruled by a ritual priesthood,"},{"time":631000,"text":"but the training for the priesthood is extraordinary."},{"time":633000,"text":"Taken from their families, sequestered in a shadowy world of darkness"},{"time":636000,"text":"for 18 years -- two nine-year periods deliberately chosen"},{"time":639000,"text":"to evoke the nine months they spend in the natural mother's womb."},{"time":642000,"text":"All that time, the world only exists as an abstraction,"},{"time":646000,"text":"as they are taught the values of their society."},{"time":648000,"text":"Values that maintain the proposition that their prayers,"},{"time":651000,"text":"and their prayers alone, maintain the cosmic balance."},{"time":654000,"text":"Now, the measure of a society is not only what it does,"},{"time":657000,"text":"but the quality of its aspirations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659000,"text":"And I always wanted to go back into these mountains,"},{"time":661000,"text":"to see if this could possibly be true,"},{"time":664000,"text":"as indeed had been reported by the great anthropologist,"},{"time":667000,"text":"Reichel-Dolmatoff."},{"time":669000,"text":"So, literally two weeks ago,"},{"time":671000,"text":"I returned from having spent six weeks with the Elder Brothers"},{"time":674000,"text":"on what was clearly the most"},{"time":676000,"text":"extraordinary trip of my life."},{"time":678000,"text":"These really are a people who live and breathe"},{"time":681000,"text":"the realm of the sacred,"},{"time":683000,"text":"a baroque religiosity that is simply awesome."},{"time":685000,"text":"They consume more coca leaves than any human population,"},{"time":688000,"text":"half a pound per man, per day."},{"time":690000,"text":"The gourd you see here is --"},{"time":693000,"text":"everything in their lives is symbolic."},{"time":696000,"text":"Their central metaphor is a loom."},{"time":698000,"text":"They say, \"Upon this loom, I weave my life.\""},{"time":700000,"text":"They refer to the movements as they exploit the ecological niches of the gradient"},{"time":703000,"text":"as \"threads.\""},{"time":705000,"text":"When they pray for the dead, they make these gestures with their hands,"},{"time":708000,"text":"spinning their thoughts into the heavens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711000,"text":"You can see the calcium buildup on the head of the poporo gourd."},{"time":714000,"text":"The gourd is a feminine aspect; the stick is a male."},{"time":717000,"text":"You put the stick in the powder"},{"time":719000,"text":"to take the sacred ashes -- well, they're not ashes,"},{"time":722000,"text":"they're burnt limestone --"},{"time":723000,"text":"to empower the coca leaf, to change"},{"time":725000,"text":"the pH of the mouth to facilitate the absorption"},{"time":727000,"text":"of cocaine hydrochloride."},{"time":729000,"text":"But if you break a gourd, you cannot simply throw it away,"},{"time":732000,"text":"because every stroke of that stick"},{"time":734000,"text":"that has built up that calcium,"},{"time":736000,"text":"the measure of a man's life,"},{"time":738000,"text":"has a thought behind it."},{"time":741000,"text":"Fields are planted in such an extraordinary way,"},{"time":743000,"text":"that the one side of the field"},{"time":745000,"text":"is planted like that by the women."},{"time":747000,"text":"The other side is planted like that by the men. Metaphorically,"},{"time":750000,"text":"you turn it on the side, and you have a piece of cloth."},{"time":753000,"text":"And they are the descendants of the ancient Tairona civilization,"},{"time":756000,"text":"the greatest goldsmiths of South America,"},{"time":757000,"text":"who in the wake of the conquest,"},{"time":759000,"text":"retreated into this isolated volcanic massif"},{"time":762000,"text":"that soars to 20,000 feet"},{"time":764000,"text":"above the Caribbean coastal plain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766000,"text":"There are four societies:"},{"time":768000,"text":"the Kogi, the Wiwa, the Kankwano and the Arhuacos."},{"time":771000,"text":"I traveled with the Arhuacos,"},{"time":773000,"text":"and the wonderful thing about this story"},{"time":775000,"text":"was that this man, Danilo Villafane --"},{"time":778000,"text":"if we just jump back here for a second."},{"time":781000,"text":"When I first met Danilo, in the Colombian embassy in Washington,"},{"time":784000,"text":"I couldn't help but say, \"You know,"},{"time":786000,"text":"you look a lot like an old friend of mine.\""},{"time":788000,"text":"Well, it turns out he was the son of my friend, Adalberto,"},{"time":791000,"text":"from 1974, who had been killed by the FARC."},{"time":794000,"text":"And I said, \"Danilo, you won't remember this,"},{"time":797000,"text":"but when you were an infant, I carried you on my back,"},{"time":799000,"text":"up and down the mountains.\""},{"time":801000,"text":"And because of that, Danilo invited us"},{"time":803000,"text":"to go to the very heart of the world,"},{"time":805000,"text":"a place where no journalist had ever been permitted."},{"time":807000,"text":"Not simply to the flanks of the mountains,"},{"time":809000,"text":"but to the very iced peaks which are the destiny of the pilgrims."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812000,"text":"And this man sitting cross-legged"},{"time":814000,"text":"is now a grown-up Eugenio,"},{"time":816000,"text":"a man who I've known since 1974."},{"time":819000,"text":"And this is one of those initiates."},{"time":821000,"text":"No, it's not true that they're kept in the darkness for 18 years,"},{"time":824000,"text":"but they are kept within the confines"},{"time":826000,"text":"of the ceremonial men's circle"},{"time":828000,"text":"for 18 years."},{"time":830000,"text":"This little boy will never step outside"},{"time":832000,"text":"of the sacred fields"},{"time":834000,"text":"that surround the men's hut for all that time,"},{"time":837000,"text":"until he begins his journey of initiation."},{"time":840000,"text":"For that entire time, the world only exists as an abstraction,"},{"time":843000,"text":"as he is taught the values of society,"},{"time":845000,"text":"including this notion that their prayers alone"},{"time":847000,"text":"maintain the cosmic balance."},{"time":850000,"text":"Before we could begin our journey,"},{"time":852000,"text":"we had to be cleansed at the portal of the Earth."},{"time":854000,"text":"And it was extraordinary to be taken by a priest."},{"time":856000,"text":"And you see that the priest never wears shoes because holy feet --"},{"time":859000,"text":"there must be nothing between the feet"},{"time":861000,"text":"and the Earth for a mamo."},{"time":864000,"text":"And this is actually the place where the Great Mother"},{"time":866000,"text":"sent the spindle into the world"},{"time":868000,"text":"that elevated the mountains and created the homeland"},{"time":870000,"text":"that they call the heart of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872000,"text":"We traveled high into the paramo,"},{"time":874000,"text":"and as we crested the hills,"},{"time":876000,"text":"we realized that the men were interpreting"},{"time":878000,"text":"every single bump on the landscape"},{"time":880000,"text":"in terms of their own intense religiosity."},{"time":883000,"text":"And then of course, as we reached our final destination,"},{"time":886000,"text":"a place called Mamancana,"},{"time":888000,"text":"we were in for a surprise,"},{"time":890000,"text":"because the FARC were waiting to kidnap us."},{"time":892000,"text":"And so we ended up being taken aside into these huts,"},{"time":895000,"text":"hidden away until the darkness."},{"time":897000,"text":"And then, abandoning all our gear,"},{"time":899000,"text":"we were forced to ride out in the middle of the night,"},{"time":902000,"text":"in a quite dramatic scene."},{"time":904000,"text":"It's going to look like a John Ford Western."},{"time":906000,"text":"And we ran into a FARC patrol at dawn, so it was quite harrowing."},{"time":909000,"text":"It will be a very interesting film. But what was fascinating"},{"time":912000,"text":"is that the minute there was a sense of dangers,"},{"time":914000,"text":"the mamos went into a circle of divination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917000,"text":"And of course, this is a photograph"},{"time":919000,"text":"literally taken the night we were in hiding,"},{"time":921000,"text":"as they divine their route"},{"time":923000,"text":"to take us out of the mountains."},{"time":925000,"text":"We were able to, because we had trained"},{"time":927000,"text":"people in filmmaking,"},{"time":929000,"text":"continue with our work,"},{"time":931000,"text":"and send our Wiwa and Arhuaco filmmakers"},{"time":934000,"text":"to the final sacred lakes"},{"time":936000,"text":"to get the last shots for the film,"},{"time":938000,"text":"and we followed the rest of the Arhuaco back to the sea,"},{"time":940000,"text":"taking the elements from the highlands to the sea."},{"time":943000,"text":"And here you see how their sacred landscape"},{"time":945000,"text":"has been covered by brothels and hotels and casinos,"},{"time":948000,"text":"and yet, still they pray."},{"time":951000,"text":"And it's an amazing thing to think"},{"time":953000,"text":"that this close to Miami,"},{"time":956000,"text":"two hours from Miami, there is an entire civilization of people"},{"time":959000,"text":"praying every day for your well-being."},{"time":962000,"text":"They call themselves the Elder Brothers."},{"time":964000,"text":"They dismiss the rest of us who have ruined the world"},{"time":967000,"text":"as the Younger Brothers. They cannot understand"},{"time":969000,"text":"why it is that we do what we do to the Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972000,"text":"Now, if we slip to another end of the world,"},{"time":974000,"text":"I was up in the high Arctic"},{"time":976000,"text":"to tell a story about global warming,"},{"time":978000,"text":"inspired in part by"},{"time":980000,"text":"the former Vice President's wonderful book."},{"time":982000,"text":"And what struck me so extraordinary"},{"time":984000,"text":"was to be again with the Inuit --"},{"time":986000,"text":"a people who don't fear the cold, but take advantage of it."},{"time":989000,"text":"A people who"},{"time":991000,"text":"find a way, with their imagination,"},{"time":993000,"text":"to carve life out of that very frozen."},{"time":996000,"text":"A people for whom blood on ice"},{"time":998000,"text":"is not a sign of death, but an affirmation of life."},{"time":1001000,"text":"And yet tragically, when you now go to those northern communities,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"you find to your astonishment"},{"time":1005000,"text":"that whereas the sea ice used to come in in September"},{"time":1007000,"text":"and stay till July,"},{"time":1009000,"text":"in a place like Kanak in northern Greenland,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"it literally comes in now in November"},{"time":1013000,"text":"and stays until March."},{"time":1015000,"text":"So, their entire year has been cut in half."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1018000,"text":"Now, I want to stress that none of these peoples"},{"time":1020000,"text":"that I've been quickly talking about here"},{"time":1022000,"text":"are disappearing worlds."},{"time":1024000,"text":"These are not dying peoples."},{"time":1026000,"text":"On the contrary, you know,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"if you have the heart to feel and the eyes to see,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"you discover that the world is not flat."},{"time":1032000,"text":"The world remains a rich tapestry."},{"time":1035000,"text":"It remains a rich topography of the spirit."},{"time":1038000,"text":"These myriad voices of humanity"},{"time":1040000,"text":"are not failed attempts at being new,"},{"time":1042000,"text":"failed attempts at being modern."},{"time":1044000,"text":"They're unique facets of the human imagination."},{"time":1046000,"text":"They're unique answers to a fundamental question:"},{"time":1049000,"text":"what does it mean to be human and alive?"},{"time":1052000,"text":"And when asked that question, they respond"},{"time":1054000,"text":"with 6,000 different voices."},{"time":1056000,"text":"And collectively, those voices become our human repertoire"},{"time":1059000,"text":"for dealing with the challenges that will confront us"},{"time":1061000,"text":"in the ensuing millennia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1063000,"text":"Our industrial society is scarcely"},{"time":1065000,"text":"300 years old."},{"time":1067000,"text":"That shallow history shouldn't suggest to anyone"},{"time":1069000,"text":"that we have all of the answers"},{"time":1071000,"text":"for all of the questions that will confront us"},{"time":1073000,"text":"in the ensuing millennia."},{"time":1075000,"text":"The myriad voices of humanity are not failed attempts at being us."},{"time":1078000,"text":"They are unique answers to that fundamental question:"},{"time":1081000,"text":"what does it mean to be human and alive?"},{"time":1083000,"text":"And there is indeed a fire burning over the Earth,"},{"time":1086000,"text":"taking with it not only plants and animals,"},{"time":1089000,"text":"but the legacy of humanity's brilliance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1091000,"text":"Right now, as we sit here in this room,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"of those 6,000 languages spoken the day that you were born,"},{"time":1096000,"text":"fully half aren't being taught to children."},{"time":1099000,"text":"So, you're living through a time"},{"time":1100000,"text":"when virtually half of humanity's intellectual,"},{"time":1103000,"text":"social and spiritual legacy"},{"time":1105000,"text":"is being allowed to slip away."},{"time":1107000,"text":"This does not have to happen."},{"time":1109000,"text":"These peoples are not failed attempts at being modern --"},{"time":1112000,"text":"quaint and colorful and destined to fade away"},{"time":1114000,"text":"as if by natural law."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1116000,"text":"In every case, these are dynamic, living peoples"},{"time":1118000,"text":"being driven out of existence by identifiable forces."},{"time":1121000,"text":"That's actually an optimistic observation,"},{"time":1124000,"text":"because it suggests that if human beings"},{"time":1126000,"text":"are the agents of cultural destruction,"},{"time":1128000,"text":"we can also be, and must be,"},{"time":1130000,"text":"the facilitators of cultural survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1132000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}